<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24607/2a.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Taft</persName> to
                                His Majesty King <persName type="to">George
                            V</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-07"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In renewing to your majesty the condolences of the American Government
                            and people upon the death of His Late Majesty I convey to you the
                            heartiest good wishes for the prosperity of your reign.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>